1
00:00:42,850 --> 00:00:48,540
♪Flower petals have fallen,
piling as high as mortal mercilessness♪

2
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:55,410
♪Gone with the wind,
as if it has never existed♪

3
00:00:56,530 --> 00:00:59,960
♪I ask for more time♪

4
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:03,290
♪To rewrite our stories♪

5
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:09,650
♪We travel together in joys and woes♪

6
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:16,470
♪Blood bathes this entangled destiny♪

7
00:01:17,110 --> 00:01:23,260
♪For the next reunion
in the troubled times♪

8
00:01:24,080 --> 00:01:27,380
♪We tread a treacherous path♪

9
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:30,640
♪To find each other♪

10
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:37,600
♪Wars and bleakness,
the bright moon shines upon the city♪

11
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:40,930
♪I will offer my bravery♪

12
00:01:41,190 --> 00:01:44,380
♪Fighting relentlessly♪

13
00:01:44,660 --> 00:01:47,630
♪All for no regrets♪

14
00:01:47,708 --> 00:01:51,348
♪In this life-and-death battle,
I will not back down♪

15
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:54,910
♪Withstand enduring time♪

16
00:01:54,910 --> 00:01:58,130
♪Someone at the end of the world
never leaves♪

17
00:01:58,270 --> 00:02:05,210
♪I brave the grim haze
to be with you once again♪

18
00:02:05,210 --> 00:02:10,950
=Love of Nirvana=
(Based on Xiao Lou's novel of the same name)

19
00:02:12,220 --> 00:02:14,000
=Episode 8=

20
00:02:17,004 --> 00:02:17,804
What are you doing?

21
00:02:18,224 --> 00:02:19,943
You don't know men.

22
00:02:22,163 --> 00:02:23,943
Candied hawthorn for sale!

23
00:02:24,943 --> 00:02:25,863
Do you want one?

24
00:02:27,344 --> 00:02:28,383
Ah, my seeds.

25
00:02:29,284 --> 00:02:29,823
Miss Jiang,

26
00:02:30,423 --> 00:02:31,084
are you all right?

27
00:02:33,883 --> 00:02:35,284
I can buy some more for you.

28
00:02:38,504 --> 00:02:39,504
I was being careless,

29
00:02:39,643 --> 00:02:41,203
I hope you don't mind, Commander Wei.

30
00:02:42,443 --> 00:02:43,763
Since you're all right,

31
00:02:44,084 --> 00:02:45,663
let's head back.

32
00:02:46,224 --> 00:02:46,804
Sure.

33
00:02:47,163 --> 00:02:48,263
Lord Pei might worry about you

34
00:02:48,643 --> 00:02:50,084
if you are out for too long.

35
00:02:57,383 --> 00:02:57,983
Your Lordship.

36
00:02:59,363 --> 00:02:59,943
Your Lordship.

37
00:03:01,363 --> 00:03:01,863
Your Lordship.

38
00:03:02,443 --> 00:03:04,084
The marketplace in Qingkang is awesome.

39
00:03:04,184 --> 00:03:05,663
I bought a lot of ingredients.

40
00:03:05,863 --> 00:03:06,624
I'm going to prepare

41
00:03:06,624 --> 00:03:08,043
some of my specialties for you.

42
00:03:09,863 --> 00:03:10,883
What's wrong with your leg?

43
00:03:13,244 --> 00:03:14,304
I wanted

44
00:03:14,423 --> 00:03:16,184
to buy some food from the market

45
00:03:16,184 --> 00:03:18,163
for your nourishment

46
00:03:18,363 --> 00:03:20,284
and also some flower seeds
to plant in the courtyard

47
00:03:20,284 --> 00:03:21,584
to make you happy.

48
00:03:22,004 --> 00:03:22,804
Unexpectedly,

49
00:03:23,103 --> 00:03:24,643
I tripped.

50
00:03:25,363 --> 00:03:26,883
How come?

51
00:03:26,983 --> 00:03:28,263
Commander Wei is to blame.

52
00:03:28,263 --> 00:03:29,363
He was trying to trick me.

53
00:03:32,784 --> 00:03:34,304
Salang won't do that to you.

54
00:03:34,663 --> 00:03:37,043
He wanted me to cook for him.

55
00:03:37,184 --> 00:03:39,524
He even bought two cabbages
to please me.

56
00:03:39,763 --> 00:03:40,763
I didn't want to go with him,

57
00:03:40,763 --> 00:03:41,684
so I refused.

58
00:03:41,823 --> 00:03:42,464
Yet

59
00:03:42,504 --> 00:03:43,943
he grabbed my hand.

60
00:03:44,143 --> 00:03:45,584
How did you respond then?

61
00:03:45,584 --> 00:03:47,124
I told him no.

62
00:03:48,483 --> 00:03:49,103
Your Lordship,

63
00:03:49,763 --> 00:03:50,464
do you think

64
00:03:50,844 --> 00:03:51,804
Commander Wei

65
00:03:51,804 --> 00:03:53,443
would play tricks on me?

66
00:03:54,163 --> 00:03:56,024
He's not a petty man.

67
00:03:59,203 --> 00:03:59,703
Lianxi,

68
00:04:00,584 --> 00:04:02,084
bring me the wound medicine
from my room.

69
00:04:05,584 --> 00:04:07,744
What did you gather

70
00:04:08,284 --> 00:04:09,363
from Tong Min and Fan Yi?

71
00:04:10,103 --> 00:04:11,504
What Deputy Commander Tong said

72
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:13,184
is aligned with your investigation.

73
00:04:13,483 --> 00:04:15,663
But there's one thing that seems odd to me.

74
00:04:15,663 --> 00:04:16,983
Deputy Commander Tong mentioned

75
00:04:17,284 --> 00:04:19,623
that when Fan Yi and he
patrolled at the back of the room,

76
00:04:19,884 --> 00:04:20,983
it was windy,

77
00:04:21,224 --> 00:04:22,623
and Fan Yi led him away.

78
00:04:23,284 --> 00:04:24,264
After that,

79
00:04:24,704 --> 00:04:26,863
when I deliberately mentioned
the back of the room to Fan Yi,

80
00:04:27,043 --> 00:04:28,524
he appeared panicked.

81
00:04:30,024 --> 00:04:30,863
The back of the room?

82
00:04:31,543 --> 00:04:31,743
Yes.

83
00:04:31,824 --> 00:04:32,644
One more thing.

84
00:04:32,964 --> 00:04:35,284
When Commander Wei
asked about the situation that night...

85
00:04:35,444 --> 00:04:36,503
I truly don't know

86
00:04:36,503 --> 00:04:38,584
how the assassin snuck in!

87
00:04:39,363 --> 00:04:41,264
He mentioned "snuck in".

88
00:04:41,264 --> 00:04:42,163
Snuck in?

89
00:04:42,784 --> 00:04:43,584
What's wrong with that?

90
00:04:43,884 --> 00:04:45,284
If he didn't know

91
00:04:45,284 --> 00:04:46,623
that the assassin would come,

92
00:04:46,964 --> 00:04:47,983
he would

93
00:04:48,264 --> 00:04:49,384
say,

94
00:04:49,824 --> 00:04:52,084
"I don't know how he got it,"

95
00:04:52,483 --> 00:04:53,683
or

96
00:04:54,243 --> 00:04:56,444
"I don't know who killed Teng Rui."

97
00:04:56,644 --> 00:04:57,983
"Snuck in" sounds too specific.

98
00:04:58,444 --> 00:04:59,603
Since the assassin snuck in,

99
00:04:59,784 --> 00:05:01,724
he must've used a very concealed way.

100
00:05:02,663 --> 00:05:03,844
That makes sense.

101
00:05:04,584 --> 00:05:05,884
But could it be too far-fetched?

102
00:05:06,284 --> 00:05:07,884
If he used the word "snuck in"

103
00:05:08,444 --> 00:05:09,324
or

104
00:05:09,543 --> 00:05:12,043
appeared panicked when he heard
about the back of the room,

105
00:05:12,163 --> 00:05:13,644
it could still be a coincidence.

106
00:05:14,003 --> 00:05:15,644
But these two points seem
rather fishy

107
00:05:15,663 --> 00:05:17,163
and make me think he's suspicious.

108
00:05:17,743 --> 00:05:18,464
I wonder

109
00:05:18,724 --> 00:05:20,503
if there's another secret passage

110
00:05:20,784 --> 00:05:22,204
that allows one to sneak into
the side manor

111
00:05:22,204 --> 00:05:23,063
without alerting anyone.

112
00:05:24,584 --> 00:05:25,603
Does Sanlang know

113
00:05:25,663 --> 00:05:26,663
about your theory?

114
00:05:27,264 --> 00:05:28,224
Of course not.

115
00:05:28,363 --> 00:05:29,503
This is serious.

116
00:05:29,503 --> 00:05:30,824
I only tell you.

117
00:05:31,103 --> 00:05:33,183
Your Lordship,
here's the wound medicine.

118
00:05:33,784 --> 00:05:34,303
Ci,

119
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:35,704
thank you so much.

120
00:05:36,243 --> 00:05:37,483
Take this wound medicine with you.

121
00:05:38,284 --> 00:05:39,144
Thank you, Your Lordship.

122
00:05:39,663 --> 00:05:41,163
I wish I could help you

123
00:05:41,224 --> 00:05:42,483
to capture the culprit
as soon as possible.

124
00:05:43,344 --> 00:05:43,983
You're injured.

125
00:05:43,983 --> 00:05:44,884
Go back to your room and rest.

126
00:05:45,224 --> 00:05:46,103
Remember to apply the medicine.

127
00:05:46,243 --> 00:05:46,704
Yes, Your Lordship.

128
00:05:47,344 --> 00:05:48,204
I'm leaving.

129
00:05:55,284 --> 00:05:55,884
Your Lordship,

130
00:05:56,644 --> 00:05:58,483
I failed to keep an eye on her.

131
00:05:58,884 --> 00:06:00,224
The east market is too crowded.

132
00:06:00,724 --> 00:06:01,724
It's my fault.

133
00:06:02,503 --> 00:06:03,503
Did you notice anything suspicious

134
00:06:03,743 --> 00:06:06,204
between Ci and Wei Zhao
when you arrived?

135
00:06:06,884 --> 00:06:07,704
No.

136
00:06:08,404 --> 00:06:09,603
As Miss Jiang said,

137
00:06:09,824 --> 00:06:11,524
they had an argument.

138
00:06:15,084 --> 00:06:16,084
By any chance,

139
00:06:17,964 --> 00:06:19,663
he's not the assassin in the tree.

140
00:06:21,103 --> 00:06:22,483
On the night
when Teng Rui was killed,

141
00:06:23,043 --> 00:06:25,204
Commander Wei and Miss Jiang
were together.

142
00:06:25,603 --> 00:06:27,024
Miss Jiang could testify for him.

143
00:06:27,204 --> 00:06:28,743
He's unlikely the murderer.

144
00:06:28,923 --> 00:06:30,483
The assassins might be someone else.

145
00:06:31,623 --> 00:06:32,803
Could it be that the clue you mentioned

146
00:06:33,243 --> 00:06:34,863
is the back of the room

147
00:06:35,483 --> 00:06:35,983
Miss Jiang said?

148
00:06:37,704 --> 00:06:38,964
If this is what Tong Min said,

149
00:06:39,444 --> 00:06:40,444
it should be true.

150
00:06:41,563 --> 00:06:42,503
Follow this clue.

151
00:06:43,524 --> 00:06:44,063
Yes, Your Lordship.

152
00:06:47,743 --> 00:06:48,644
(Shameless Cat,)

153
00:06:49,084 --> 00:06:50,464
(since you don't believe in curses)

154
00:06:50,464 --> 00:06:51,584
(or promises,)

155
00:06:51,964 --> 00:06:53,003
(I won't trust you either.)

156
00:06:53,764 --> 00:06:56,003
(I only agreed to clear your name,)

157
00:06:56,003 --> 00:06:57,384
(but I didn't promise
that I wouldn't tell His Lordship)

158
00:06:57,384 --> 00:06:58,444
(about the murderer.)

159
00:06:58,863 --> 00:06:59,663
(No matter what,)

160
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:02,923
(I must get my clay cat back.)

161
00:07:19,204 --> 00:07:21,144
Lord Pei, you called me at short notice.

162
00:07:21,183 --> 00:07:22,423
Are there any discoveries?

163
00:07:23,243 --> 00:07:25,284
According to the statement
of Tong Min and Fan Yi,

164
00:07:25,644 --> 00:07:26,584
I suspect

165
00:07:26,764 --> 00:07:29,663
that the murderer entered
the side manor through a secret passage.

166
00:07:30,404 --> 00:07:31,103
Secret passage?

167
00:07:32,603 --> 00:07:33,844
Back then, my father chose

168
00:07:33,844 --> 00:07:35,284
to build a side manor
on this land

169
00:07:35,284 --> 00:07:36,923
because of the water source

170
00:07:37,243 --> 00:07:38,784
and using the river of a moat.

171
00:07:39,043 --> 00:07:41,183
Qinghui River flows through
the entire Qingkang City

172
00:07:41,303 --> 00:07:42,944
with an interconnected water system.

173
00:07:43,964 --> 00:07:45,363
Do you suspect that the murderer

174
00:07:45,603 --> 00:07:48,183
snuck in through the river?

175
00:07:49,363 --> 00:07:51,584
But the walls are tall,

176
00:07:51,803 --> 00:07:53,543
and the soldiers take turns
to guard the place day and night.

177
00:07:53,784 --> 00:07:54,623
Even though the murderer

178
00:07:54,623 --> 00:07:56,183
snuck in through the river,

179
00:07:56,344 --> 00:07:58,384
how did he manage
to get into the side manor?

180
00:08:02,423 --> 00:08:03,743
Do you suspect

181
00:08:03,863 --> 00:08:06,224
that the murderer came in

182
00:08:06,663 --> 00:08:07,663
through this sewer outlet?

183
00:08:08,344 --> 00:08:10,183
All private residences
built by the river

184
00:08:10,563 --> 00:08:12,144
have the key.

185
00:08:12,603 --> 00:08:13,344
As for the rest,

186
00:08:13,384 --> 00:08:15,103
they are kept
in the Maintenance Bureau.

187
00:08:15,503 --> 00:08:17,503
But the sprawling underground drainage
is interconnected.

188
00:08:18,003 --> 00:08:19,303
With one opening hole,

189
00:08:19,603 --> 00:08:20,983
one could enter the side manor

190
00:08:21,363 --> 00:08:22,303
through the underground drain.

191
00:08:23,423 --> 00:08:23,923
Your Lordship,

192
00:08:25,123 --> 00:08:25,904
we found something over there.

193
00:09:00,684 --> 00:09:01,424
We looked into this.

194
00:09:03,143 --> 00:09:05,204
The Maintenance Bureau was caught
in a fire ten days ago.

195
00:09:05,204 --> 00:09:06,523
The chaos lasted for about two hours.

196
00:09:07,143 --> 00:09:08,184
We believe

197
00:09:08,283 --> 00:09:10,304
that the murderer stole the key

198
00:09:10,444 --> 00:09:11,544
and forged a duplicate.

199
00:09:11,883 --> 00:09:12,804
On the night of the fire,

200
00:09:13,143 --> 00:09:14,684
he entered through a manhole
by the river

201
00:09:15,103 --> 00:09:16,804
to the side minor
to commit murder and set fire,

202
00:09:17,143 --> 00:09:18,283
then he returned the same way.

203
00:09:19,584 --> 00:09:20,804
These threads

204
00:09:21,044 --> 00:09:22,123
were likely caught

205
00:09:22,123 --> 00:09:23,263
from his clothes

206
00:09:23,304 --> 00:09:24,424
when he entered the river.

207
00:09:25,224 --> 00:09:26,483
Did you find anything about the threads?

208
00:09:26,844 --> 00:09:28,684
It matches the belt fabric
of the assassin

209
00:09:28,684 --> 00:09:30,283
in the peace negotiation.

210
00:09:30,544 --> 00:09:31,964
It's called Yunjin.

211
00:09:32,084 --> 00:09:33,603
This fabric has recently been sold
mostly to Wei State.

212
00:09:34,523 --> 00:09:35,304
Wei State?

213
00:09:35,743 --> 00:09:37,544
Could it be the Wei people

214
00:09:37,664 --> 00:09:38,584
who murdered Teng Rui?

215
00:09:41,783 --> 00:09:43,564
Judging from the size and depth
of the boot print,

216
00:09:43,804 --> 00:09:46,023
the body size of the assassin
and the murderer don't match.

217
00:09:46,603 --> 00:09:49,084
They are not the same person?

218
00:09:49,643 --> 00:09:51,084
But for one to enter the side minor

219
00:09:51,084 --> 00:09:52,103
through the underground drain,

220
00:09:52,424 --> 00:09:54,103
they must be good at swimming.

221
00:09:54,724 --> 00:09:55,983
There's an expert in Wei State

222
00:09:56,424 --> 00:09:58,143
who can kill underwater.

223
00:09:58,283 --> 00:10:00,304
This person once has a grudge
against Teng Rui.

224
00:10:00,603 --> 00:10:01,804
Where is this person now?

225
00:10:02,084 --> 00:10:03,363
They disappeared half a year ago.

226
00:10:03,664 --> 00:10:04,103
Your Lordship,

227
00:10:04,523 --> 00:10:05,903
the deadline is in two days.

228
00:10:06,424 --> 00:10:07,964
If we report to His Majesty
that it's an internal power struggle,

229
00:10:08,143 --> 00:10:09,283
we can save Tong Min.

230
00:10:11,584 --> 00:10:12,103
Your Lordship...

231
00:10:19,603 --> 00:10:20,304
Commander An,

232
00:10:20,763 --> 00:10:21,763
this case involves many parties.

233
00:10:22,483 --> 00:10:24,204
I believe Lord Pei
has his own consideration.

234
00:10:24,883 --> 00:10:25,544
How about

235
00:10:26,023 --> 00:10:26,983
we leave for now?

236
00:10:58,564 --> 00:10:59,143
Cui.

237
00:10:59,863 --> 00:11:00,464
Ci.

238
00:11:00,724 --> 00:11:01,964
I made some pastry

239
00:11:02,103 --> 00:11:03,263
for you.

240
00:11:03,564 --> 00:11:04,444
Thank you, Ci.

241
00:11:04,564 --> 00:11:05,804
But I don't eat

242
00:11:05,844 --> 00:11:06,804
when I'm reading.

243
00:11:07,084 --> 00:11:08,763
I don't want to dirty the books.

244
00:11:09,204 --> 00:11:11,363
Cui, you cherish the books so much.

245
00:11:11,763 --> 00:11:13,143
The weather is nice today.

246
00:11:13,143 --> 00:11:15,464
Why not take all your books outside
to sun them?

247
00:11:15,844 --> 00:11:17,084
I saw many worms in your book

248
00:11:17,184 --> 00:11:19,044
when I visited you last time.

249
00:11:19,924 --> 00:11:20,584
Sounds good.

250
00:11:21,044 --> 00:11:22,164
If so, I'm heading back.

251
00:11:23,743 --> 00:11:24,743
Please look after

252
00:11:24,944 --> 00:11:25,863
Commander Wei.

253
00:11:26,584 --> 00:11:26,863
Sure.

254
00:11:27,023 --> 00:11:27,883
Don't worry, Cui.

255
00:11:39,783 --> 00:11:41,224
I knew you would come.

256
00:11:43,304 --> 00:11:44,243
What did you bring?

257
00:11:46,804 --> 00:11:47,844
Ah, rice cake. That's nice.

258
00:11:48,143 --> 00:11:49,084
It's simple

259
00:11:49,403 --> 00:11:50,483
and sweet.

260
00:12:01,424 --> 00:12:02,603
You have good teeth.

261
00:12:03,924 --> 00:12:04,704
You are using me.

262
00:12:06,003 --> 00:12:06,964
Am I using you?

263
00:12:07,924 --> 00:12:09,044
What makes you think that way?

264
00:12:09,164 --> 00:12:10,584
You used me to mislead His Lordship

265
00:12:11,003 --> 00:12:13,403
and others into believing
that the murderer is someone else.

266
00:12:13,503 --> 00:12:14,883
The secret passage behind the room,

267
00:12:15,464 --> 00:12:16,763
those threads,

268
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:18,044
and the footprint of the murderer.

269
00:12:18,263 --> 00:12:19,783
These are all the smokescreens
you prepared.

270
00:12:20,403 --> 00:12:22,023
The master doesn't exist at all.

271
00:12:22,523 --> 00:12:23,643
The one who has been manipulating
everything behind the scenes

272
00:12:23,643 --> 00:12:24,783
is you.

273
00:12:24,783 --> 00:12:26,143
You are Xiao Wuxia.

274
00:12:28,243 --> 00:12:29,603
Could you explain to me

275
00:12:30,084 --> 00:12:31,184
how I made those arrangements?

276
00:12:32,103 --> 00:12:33,084
Tong Min wouldn't lie.

277
00:12:33,743 --> 00:12:35,103
It's true that he went
to the back of the room

278
00:12:35,103 --> 00:12:36,344
with Fan Yi.

279
